<h2 class="bold font-l">Ratigan's Death Trap</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
(The Image Source for the Trope) As it turns out, Ratigan had so many different ideas for how to kill Basil, he decided to use all of them, in an elaborate and over-the-top Rube Goldberg Device. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="2u7pjw" data-video-descrip="Wile E. Coyote sets up a complex Rube Goldberg device in his final attempt to catch the Road Runner. Guess who becomes a victim to the trap instead..." data-video-title="Hook, Line and Stinker" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/2u7pjw_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/2u7pjw.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/RubeGoldbergHatesYourGuts" data-video-tropename="Rube Goldberg Hates Your Guts" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/LooneyTunes,WesternAnimation/WileECoyoteAndTheRoadrunner,WesternAnimation/HookLineAndStinker" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/2u7pjw.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Hook, Line and ...</span></p>
</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
